<section>
  <h1>Enter a context-free grammar</h1>

  <p>For example:</p>

  <pre>
S -> id | V assign E .
V -> id .
E -> V | num .</pre>
</section>

<section>
  <h1>Analyze the grammar</h1>

  <p>Click Analyze to run the analysis.</p>

  <p>This does basic sanity checks, computes properties of nonterminals, and classifies the grammar according to parsing algorithm. You can also generate parsing tables and automata diagrams.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h1>Transform the grammar</h1>
  
  <p>Click Transform to switch to transformation mode.</p>

  <p>Apply grammar transformations interactively: remove immediate left recursion, left-factor productions, perform epsilon-separation, and remove unreachable nonterminals.</p>
</section>
